For web files, the fundamental principle is to only download what you need.

We avoid breaking changes as much as possible.

But there are some small upgrades we are introducing in preparation for v1.

Like to use frame utilities you will access them from /onchainkit/frame going forward.

It's not quite documented yet, but you will always have access to a "core" namespace which will have access to features that have zero requirements.

So, feel free to do `import { ... } from '/onchainkit/core'` and you will get all the features that are pure TS without requirements.
If in "core" is missing anything you need, let me know and we can add it.

Alright, today with `v0.11.3` we exposed on OnchainKit the:
- getName: https://onchainkit.xyz/identity/get-name
- getAvatar: https://onchainkit.xyz/identity/get-avatar
utilities to assist in retrieving name and avatar identity information.

These utilities come in handy when working with Next.js or any Node.js backend.

One thing we are planning for is ensuring that both getName and getAvatar are not only user-friendly for ENS, but also for Nouns.

Ideally, if you have an address, you should be able to display any social identity of your choice.
